in all of these, the sorting methods are defined as a function taking in an array or a pointer to the start of an array and a len

Languages using example_sort(array)
python

Languages using example_sort(pointer to start, length of array)
c++


The Following sorting methods are implemented and can all be called in the forms above

Bubble sort: bubble_sort(array) or bubble_sort(pointer to start, length of array)
Insertion sort: insertion_sort(array) or insertion_sort(pointer to start, length of array)
Merge sort: merge_sort(array) or merge_sort(pointer to start, length of array)
Quick sort: quick_sort(array) or quick_sort(pointer to start, length of array)